(
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FF7AFF62FEAEB395" box="[159,287,186,211]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 27–32</figureCitation>
