<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FF72FEDAFE0AB25E" authority="Becker, 1911: 98" authorityName="Becker, Elachiptera Macquart" authorityPageNumber="98" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,443,258,280]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Disciphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FF72FEDAFF4DB25E" box="[151,252,258,280]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Disciphus</emphasis>
Becker, 1911: 98
</taxonomicName>
. Type species: 
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FDBAFEDAFD0EB25E" box="[607,703,258,280]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Disciphis</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FD2DFEDBFC76B25E" authority="Becker, 1911" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1911" box="[712,967,258,280]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Disciphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FD2DFEDBFC84B25E" box="[712,821,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">peregrinus</emphasis>
Becker, 1911
</taxonomicName>
(subsequent designation by Sabrosky, 1941: 752).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C352655BFF804133FF72FEBCFE82B2E6" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF72FEBCFE82B2E6" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FF72FEBCFEA0B23B" bold="true" box="[151,273,356,381]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FEF9FEBCFE19B23B" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[284,424,356,381]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oscinellinae">Oscinellinae</taxonomicName>
with a patterned wing, a trapezoidal scutellum with a pair of long tubercles and long slender arista.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C352655BFF804133FF22FE74FCFAB662" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF22FE74FC15B13E" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FF22FE74FEE8B283" bold="true" box="[199,345,428,453]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FE85FE74FE5FB283" box="[352,494,428,453]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FE1FFE74FD3BB283" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[506,650,428,453]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oscinellinae">Oscinellinae</taxonomicName>
. Vertex rounded in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FC1BFE74FBE2B282" box="[1022,1107,428,453]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); frontal triangle shining and bare; frons microtomentose; cephalic chaetotaxy: long peristomal bristles, cruciate postocellar bristles, cruciate short ocellar bristles, long outer vertical setae, interfrontal setulae long and on inner margin of frontal triangle, orbital bristles reclinate, one longer than others; eye sparsely and microscopically pubescent; gena narrow, vibrissal angle rounded, indistinct; face flat, wide, carina absent; first flagellomere reniform, higher than wide, arista longer than width of frons, and slender (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FDEFFD87FDEFB13E" box="[522,606,607,632]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); proboscis and palpus short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF22FD5CFBBEB0DE" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Scutum square, as wide as long; thoracic chaetotaxy: 1 anterior, 1 posterior notopleurals, 1 postsutural supraalar bristle, 1 dorsocentral bristle; scutellum flat dorsally, trapezoidal, usually wider than long, with a pair of very long scutellar tubercles (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FE4CFD14FE4CB1A2" box="[425,509,716,741]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); 1 pair apical scutellar bristles, 1 pair of lateral scutellar bristles; thoracic pleurites bare except for a row of setulae on katepisternum. Wing long, narrow, with a pattern, second costal sector equal or longer than third costal sector, distance between crossvein r-m and dm-cu 3.5 times length of dm-cu, anal angle reduced, alula small, much longer than wide; veins dark; halter white (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FC3BFCEFFB86B016" box="[990,1079,823,848]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Legs long and slender; male femoral organ present as 1–3 rows of 8–10 tubercles; small, apical ventral spur on mid tibia; hind tibial spur absent; tibial organ oval, sometimes very narrow, 0.2 to 0.25 times length of hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF22FC7CFA2CB0A6" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Abdomen slender, abdominal tergites setulose laterally and with sparse setae posteriorly, mostly microtomentose; sternites slender, with sparse setae; male spiracles 
<quantity id="4CB09B35FF804133FC68FC1FFC65B0A6" box="[909,980,967,992]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" metricValueMax="1.27" metricValueMin="0.762" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="in" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 in</quantity>
membrane near lateral margin of tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF22FC34FABFB7D3" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Male postabdomen: pregenital sclerites narrow; spiracles 6 and 
<quantity id="4CB09B35FF804133FC4EFC35FC68B743" box="[939,985,1004,1029]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
membrane ventral to lateral margin of dorsal sclerite; epandrium rounded, usually higher than long in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FBC1FBD7FBCBB76E" box="[1060,1146,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) and wider than high in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF804133FEB6FBECFE1AB70A" box="[339,427,1076,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1397,494,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1436,483,1895]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Disciphus peregrinus. 27. Head, lateral; 28. Antenna; 29. Wing; 30. Scutellum, dorsal; 31. Male genitalia, posterior; 32. Male genitalia, lateral. Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars—Fig. 29 = 0.5 mm; Figs 28, 30–31 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439425/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); surstylus simple, parallel sided; hypandrium open posteriorly; pregonite fused with postgonite, weakly sclerotized; basiphallus elongate, weakly sclerotized; distiphallus short, membranous; phallapodeme simple; phallic 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FE02FBA4FD94B7D3" box="[487,549,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Anatrichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guide">guide</taxonomicName>
sclerotized; cercus small, rectangular, projecting posteroventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF22FB47FC77B7FE" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" box="[199,966,1183,1208]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Female terminalia not modified, cerci separate, cylindrical, setulose.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF804133FF22FB1CFCFAB662" blockId="18.[151,1437,356,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FF22FB1CFE5EB79B" bold="true" box="[199,495,1220,1245]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FE10FB1CFDD4B79B" authorityName="Becker, Elachiptera Macquart" authorityYear="1911" box="[501,613,1220,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Disciphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FE10FB1CFDD4B79B" box="[501,613,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Disciphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Oriental realm. As previously defined, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FF59FB3FFE9DB646" authorityName="Becker, Elachiptera Macquart" authorityYear="1911" box="[188,300,1255,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Disciphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FF59FB3FFE9DB646" box="[188,300,1255,1280]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Disciphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also included the Palearctic region (Japan); however, based our analysis, the Japanese species (
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FF45FAD4FE1AB663" authorityName="Kanmiya" authorityYear="1983" box="[160,427,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Disciphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subelongatus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FF45FAD4FE1AB663" box="[160,427,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Disciphus subelongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) has been transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF804133FD25FAD4FCF5B663" authorityName="Macquart, Melanochaeta Bezzi" authorityYear="1835" box="[704,836,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Elachiptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF804133FD25FAD4FCF5B663" box="[704,836,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Elachiptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
